
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `autoscan` baraye jostojo va peida kardan otomatike device-ha va service-ha dar yek shabake (network) be kar miravad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta device-ha va service-haye mojud ra bedune dastkari ziad peida konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `autoscan -t [IP address]`  --> 🎯 Scan kardan ye IP address khass.
    🔹 `autoscan -p [port number]` --> 🚪 Scan kardan port-e khass.
    🔹 `autoscan -r [IP range]`   --> 🌐 Scan kardan yek range IP address.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ autoscan
    
    🔹 Shorooe scan baraye device-ha va service-ha dar shabake mahali (local network).

    $ autoscan -t 192.168.1.10
    
    🔹 Scan kardan faghat IP address 192.168.1.10.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ autoscan -p 80,443
    
    🔹 Scan kardan port-haye 80 va 443 baraye device-ha va service-ha.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `autoscan` command is used for automatically discovering devices and services on a network. It helps you quickly identify available devices and services without extensive manual configuration.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `autoscan -t [IP address]`  --> 🎯 Scan a specific IP address.
    🔹 `autoscan -p [port number]` --> 🚪 Scan a specific port number.
    🔹 `autoscan -r [IP range]`   --> 🌐 Scan a range of IP addresses.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ autoscan
    
    🔹 Start scanning for devices and services on the local network.

    $ autoscan -t 192.168.1.10
    
    🔹 Scan only the IP address 192.168.1.10.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ autoscan -p 80,443
    
    🔹 Scan ports 80 and 443 for devices and services.
